-- U.S. Gasoline Fell 15 Cents to $3.48 a Gallon in Lundberg Survey
-- B y   B a r b a r a   P o w e l l   a n d   J u l i e   J o h n s s o n
-- 2012-06-24T18:28:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/u-s-gasoline-fell-15-cents-to-3-48-a-gallon-in-lundberg-survey.html
The average price of regular
gasoline at U.S. filling stations declined 15 cents in the past
two weeks to $3.48 a gallon, according to Lundberg Survey Inc.  The survey covers the period ended June 22 and is based on
information received from about 2,500 stations by the Camarillo,
California-based company. The price is down 49 cents from the
highest average this year, during the two weeks ended April 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
